# Bump the integer below to invalidate every Bitbucket pipeline cache
# (`cargo`, `target`, `target-cov`, `rustup`). Useful when:
#   - a major dep was added and the cargo registry cache is missing it
#     (Bitbucket caches are immutable per key — once populated they
#     don't auto-update for new crates)
#   - target/ accumulated stale artifacts after a long stretch of patch
#     bumps and incremental rebuilds
#
# Bumping the integer changes this file's content hash, which changes
# the derived cache key, which forces Bitbucket to upload a fresh
# cache on the next run (and then freeze that one until the next bump).
1
